values: I'm still alive! *g* And I'm right on time to say MERRY CHRISTMAS! :) I got a bunch of new pictures I wanna share. took most of them today since everything looked really gorgeous outside. I couldn't keep my hands off the camera. preview:

Shame on me. In my last entry I said that I was gonna post more of my pics REAL SOON. haha, well that didn't work out ... you know me. So I won't write anything like that again. Let's just see. However, I'll post everything I can find and still hope to get some comments even if my updates are that irregular. I took all this photos together with a good friend of mine, so credit goes to him, too. ;) cloudy sunset......the colors of fall...shadows cloudy sunset the colors of fall shadows

Almost a month later ... but I'm still alive. :P Just not online that often. My 6 weeks of vacation are over and this is my second week at school. Slowly but surely everything is getting back to normal. However, I wanted to post some of my newest pics. There are some quite a lot I'd like to share so I wont post them all in this post. I'll start with 'sunset at the pond'. Teaser

It's time for some rambling. =P I'm freaking out here ... seriously. There's this guy. And well, we both know that we 'like' each other. The problem is that he's not saying / doing ANYTHING and that really pisses me off. xD I WON'T be the one running after HIM. No way. I celebrated my 16th birthday on Friday ... that would've been the best opportunity ever ... but NO, of course we keep grinning at each other without saying a thing. xD *sighs* Boys are stupid. Okay, enough of that. ^^ I took some pictures on a Tuesday morning. The light was awesome. ^^ I couldn't help but think of *fields of gold*. :) I post only four pics but I actually think they're worth looking at them. ^^

There's some new stuff posted over at . Guys, I cannot describe how unbelievably bored I am. School's been awful: wrote a french test, got back a maths test (which was under our average), got back our music test, had to write characterizations ... URGH.

So I snagged this from <lj user="odakota_rose"> to keep me from dying of boredom. xD

Rule # 1:
You are NOT ALLOWED to explain ANYTHING unless someone
messages you and asks

Rule #2:
Only answer True or False

<lj-cut text='Nobody said it was easy. No one ever said it would be this hard.'>
Q: Kissed one of your closest friends--> false
Q: Been arrested?--> false
Q: Kissed someone you didn't like?--> false
Q: You like someone?--> true
Q: Held a snake?--> false
Q: Been suspended from school?--> false
Q: Kissed in the rain?--> false
Q: Sang in the shower?--> true

Q: Made a girlfriend/boyfriend cry?--> false

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
"Who was your last?"
just be 100% truthful
LAST PERSON.

1. You hung out with?--> Tine (mh truthful huh? - Isa? ;) )
2. Last person you texted?--> Julian
3. You were in a car with?--> Dominik
4. Went to the movies with?--> Tine
5. Went to the mall with?--> Tine
6. You talked to on the phone?--> Christina
7. Made you laugh? --> Joel
8. You hugged?--> My Mom
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
WOULD YOU RATHER...
(NUMBER ONE IS MISSING!?)
2. Be serious or be funny?--> Funny
3. Drink whole or skim milk?--> Whole milk
4. Die in a fire or get shot?--> get shot, I guess :P
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ANSWER TRUTHFULLY...

1. Sun or moon?--> Sun

2. Winter or Fall?--> Fall

3. Left or right?--> Right

4. Sunny or rainy? Sunny

FIVE IS MISSING! WTF?

6. Where do you live? Germany

OMG 7 IS MISSING TOO!

8. Do you want to get married? Yeah I think so

9. Do you twirl your spaghetti or cut it? Twirling it. ^^

10. Do You Cook? rarely 

11. Current mood? bored and depressed

IN THE LAST 72 HOURS HAVE YOU...

1. Kissed someone? No

2. Sang? Yes

3. Been hugged? Yes

4. Like someone you can't have? dunno


WOAH. A NAME MEME
what is your name: Alicia

spell it backwards: Aicila

spell it with your elbow: alica

spell it with your eyes shut: alicia

spell it with your forehead: aqlo8idf8q

spell it with your nose: alicia

spell it with your chin: al,ik kiya


... I feel stupid now. xD

Hi! Yay, my day was great. As soon as the sun's shining I'm in a better mood. ^^ School was totally relaxed today. We've been working on a video project for two weeks now and today we were the first group to finish our vid. I'm surprised!! I didn't expect it to be that good. xD *is happy* Made some new icons and stuff, too. I just posted it over at #Icons [09] Tate (An Eye for an Eye) #Banner [02] Booth/Brennan #Teaser #Important Info + credit + If you want to use some credit or + Comments are love (the special two)

Urgh, my day was really stressful... - glad it's almost over. ^^ I've been at school until about 4pm, had singing lessons afterwards an came home at about 6pm. I hate those long days. Well and then I just felt like watching JAG xD. So I decided to look for the DVD's I burned for saving data and WOW, I really found it. That's really some kind of a miracle considerning the mess in my cupboard. Be proud of me. ;) I rediscovered my very first fanvid and thought I have to upload it. ^^ I still love the song and I enjoyed watching my favourite shipper scenes. (I haven't watched JAG in ages!) sorry, don't know who made this one!

Just watched wednesday night's episode of Bones! *grins* I couldn't resist. I simply HAD to make up some icons. :) #Icons [10] Bones (2.22 - Stargazer in a Puddle) #Teaser #Important Info + credit + Comments are love (Never leave my side)

Yay, I rather finally found a new layout. I'm not saying I didn't like the old one anymore but it was simply time for something new. Thanks to again! Love the layout. It's so girly. ;) Any news? ... let's see: I'm an ICON-MAKER at , a veery nice community by . I'm so glad I can post my icons and stuff there. :) I posted Tate and Bones Icons over there yesterday. So everyone: Take a look and comment! ^^ Teaser: (follow the fake cut)

First of all: Happy Easter to all of you. ^^ I hope you enjoyed the day. I went out to take some new photos since it's already starting to become pretty green outside. I love spring!!! It's my favoutite time of the year. Everytings so bright and colourful. I hope my pics represent that. ^^ I've mostly taken macros. Would be great to get some feedback. ;)

YAY! I'm FINALLY able to use Adobe Photoshop!! Ok, I probably have to define "be able to use". xD I still don't understand how to use these layers and stuff. That really needs some time getting used to if you normally work with Microsoft Picture it! ;) But I'll get along. Just need a few more boring evenings on which I have enough time to try and test everything. Well, since yesterday was one of these boring evenings I now proudly present my very first icon made with ps. *g* I kinda like it. By the way: I still got lots of snow - photographs waiting to be uploaded, so I guess I'll post again pretty soon.

Okay, I've got some time now. So I thought I'd start with the photos I took in January. In that week you could have thought that it's March or April ... the weather was kind of odd. ^^ Would you pleeease leave a comment if you like them? ^^ That would be great.

Hey there,

I'm back ... finally. My computers works, what a miracle. 

Well, there's not really a lot to tell, I guess. The last few weeks have been crap and I'm just a little pissed off of life right now. Too many things are going wrong. Whatever, let's just hope that this is not gonna become status quo. 
Oh, by the way, did I mention that parents suck? - Now, it did. And it's true. I'll go to bed now.

I still have some new photographs waiting to be uploaded but I simply feel like sleeping now.

Good night.

MY COMPUTER SUCKS!

It doesn't work at the moment, so I'm not gonna be able to post here that often. I'm now using my mom's laptop, so I don't have my stuff here. That kinda pisses me of. :P

Just wanted to post the info. ^^

Here they are. I took some close-up views from frost on a wonderful decemberday with my new cam last year. =P Let me know what you think. These are the first photos of that kind that I've taken up to now. Of course, I would love to get some constructive reviews. ;)

...again ... I haven't posted here in ages, I know. I just don't seem to have a lot to tell. *g* Well, I decided to upload my new photos soon. I've taken lots of new ones and I think some of them are quite good. ;) Since I have one more week vacation I guess I'll find some time. 

But what I basically wanted to say was: OKAY, Isa finally made it. I am hooked! We watched a few Bones eppies when I was at her place in Berlin and WOW, I love Bones. *g* Great series. Took a while longer til I got that. *g* Now I'm watching the same Bones-vid over and over again.


Happy new year to all of you, by the way.

hugs,
Liz
